description:
Months after the deranged scientist known as Clockwork attempted to reduce to ashes – insane vengeance for the senseless death of this son – the people that call the city home set about the task of rebuilding. The squad of protectors, The Nevermen, have lost two of their own, Diggs and McKay, in battle. Reduced now to a trio, the trenchcoated toughs must face a new evil simmering beneath the city. What hell will this reawakened villain unleash? Which crime bosses will compose his army? Can The Nevermen be victorious without the help of the anti-hero/bounty hunter, the Murderist?

Journey again, to a time when the action was bold, evil seductive, and the good guys wore suits...
name: Part 1

description:
The sinister Winterbone has been unearthed from his chamber-grave beneath the streets, assembled his henchmen, and is poised to take the city as his own. With some of his criminal cohorts still behind bars, he hatches a plan to free them, and unleash a chilling prologue to his masterful scheme. The Nevermen, though weakened in number, have sworn to protect the city, even at the cost of their own lives. They’ll take to the skies and the alleys to defeat all weird foes… and enlist allies if they can’t.

But trouble is bubbling like blood.
name: Part 2

description:
The new-and-improved Cadaver wasn’t enough to defeat The Nevermen. Problem is, he’s not the only villain newly freed from prison and running amuck in . The infernal Mr. Match has no problem sparking a conflict with the city’s official heroes. The creepy fish-goon Samek is up for skewering a do-gooder or two. And the feral Neverman is an amoral wild card, created to win a fight. But Winterbone is their general in this urban war. He’ll let his boys have their fun, but the real prize is nothing less than control of the city itself.

If the Nevermen can’t protect the city, is there another hero that can?
name: Part 3

description: Second Real Ghostbusters Annual.
name: Ghostbusters Annual 1990

description: The original four short stories that introduced Buck Godot, the futuristic gun for hire who is always available, but never free. This collection is an excellent introduction to Buck and the controlled anarchy that is Hong Kong, a planet where the only law is that there is not law. Find out why Buck Godot remains one of Phil Foglio's most popular creations.

volume.name: Buck Godot: Zap Gun for Hire

description:
BIG TIME concludes for the biggest criminal in the Marvel Universe!

FREE OSBORN! The former Green Goblin, Iron Patriot and war-criminal director of H.A.M.M.E.R. gets his day in the sun, as the atrocities of his top-secret incarceration are revealed. Norman Osborn stands poised to win the day…will the super villain walk free to plague the Marvel Universe again?
name: Part 5

description: 'Keys to the Kingdom' comes to a close-as Dodge and Tyler Locke confront one another at last. Tyler came armed with the truth; Dodge prefers sharper instruments, and shows his willingness to use them, in a story that will tear more than one life to shreds...
name: Detectives, Part 2

volume.name: Locke & Key: Keys to the Kingdom

description: Last Issue
name: Julius Caesar: Super Genius!

description: BRAND NEW ARC. GREAT FOR NEW READERS! Kurt Busiek continues to bring an incredibly modern spin to the Dracula mythos! As Dracula and Conrad's fight reaches a fever pitch, Evan enters into an unlikely, and dangerous alliance with Marta and her men. It's vampire vs. vampire vs. vampire hunters as the ongoing horror series from the mind of Kurt Busiek continues!

New York City: It's the roaring 20s and America's great metropolis has become the nexus of high society culture, cutting edge industry and perhaps the most shocking crime wave in our country's history. Known for its sinister and treacherous underworld, there's a new power waking up the city that never sleeps. Its name... John 'The Hand' Smith. The Nickname is a given. An outcast and an orphan, Smith's massive right hand is nearly twice as large as his left, and when push comes to shove, you'd pity anyone that's gets in his way. Smith's only friends in the world are a fellow orphan and low-rent black gangster nicknamed Bootsy, and a Asian femme fatale known as Ring-a-Ling. In a world of crime, passion, and a touch of the fantastic, they will attempt to change organized crime... or die trying.

John 'The Hand' Smith may have escaped the jeweled jaws of Diamond Jack, but his troubles only seem to multiply. Someone is hell bent on seeing Smith and his oversized northpaw dispatched to their maker. But what doesn't kill him only seems to make him stronger, and Smith convinces Boss Madden to undertake a dangerous plan to rob the Chinese gangs of their opium, only to sell it back at an enormous profit. But double-crossings and Tommy guns wreak havoc on the Madden Crime Organization and just as things go from bad to worse, Madden's girl, Cora, starts to wonder if what they say about men with big hands is really true.

In spite of the several public attempts on his life, Smith charges ahead with his plan to steal an opium shipment to the Chinese and then sell it back to them for a song. But when Smith, Bootsy and Ring-a-Ling are surprised by the Italians on the roofs of Chinatown, the only way out is through a wall of Chinese gangsters, who don't need guns to do serious damage. Neither does Cora, boss Madden's moll, who's got Smith all hot under the collar. But are her advances simply those of a flirtatious flapper, or is there something else going on behind the heart-stopping allure of the boss' girl?

The entire New York City underworld has gone topsy-turvy. Mob boss Mad Dog Madden is in hiding now that his original made-man, Gentleman Jim, is in the dog house. But when the Irish Mobster posts a reward for anyone that can bring him the right hand of the Dock Walloper, the war that's been brewing in the great melting pot is about to boil over!
name: West Side Dry

description: Sometimes good police work just isn’t enough, as Inspector Thomas Adye of Scotland Yard finds out when he’s assigned to the Jack the Ripper case. He’ll need the guidance of imprisoned madman and amoral libertine, Dr. Henry Jekyll, whose mind-splitting serum Jack might be using to commit his bloody murders. Written by Cole Haddon and illustrated by M.S. Corley, part 1 of Hyde sets in motion events that will pit London’s two greatest monsters against one another. Will Adye--and his soul--survive intact?
name: 1 (of 4)

volume.name: The Strange Case of Mr. Hyde

description: It is a question that man has long asked-are we alone in the universe? This?February, the United Nations Space Command learns the answer to that question... and unfortunately, the answer is NO. Catch the beginning of the struggle between Man and Covenant in this epic series based on the novel by Eric Nylund, adapted by Brian Reed, and brought brilliantly to life by Felix Ruiz!
name: Covenant, Chapter 1

description:
The smash-hit Eisner-nominated collection from Shannon Wheeler I THOUGHT YOU WOULD BE FUNNIER features the best-of-the-best of what's left on the cutting room floor from critically acclaimed Shannon Wheeler's cartoon submissions to The New Yorker Magazine. Shannon has won a dedicated following through his cartoons for The New Yorker, The Onion, and his own creation, Too Much Coffee Man.

An Eisner-Nominated comic by Shannon Wheeler dealing with life issues. Comics are in "New Yorker" style drawings and captions.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: I Thought You Would Be Funnier

description:
Daredevil legend Joe Quesada crafts a mystery set during the deadliest heat wave in NYC history. A serial killer is on the loose, pushing a city already past its breaking point over the edge, and Daredevil must battle the heat and fear to keep a crumbling Hell's Kitchen together...by any means necessary!

Collects Daredevil: Father (2004) #1-6.
name: HC/TPB

description: Rex and Bobo's roughhousing leads to a an accident in Doc Holiday's lab, temporarily turning Rex into the mechanically-monstrous EVO he was never meant to be! Does Bobo have what it takes to change his friend back, or will Six have to ground them both forever?
name: Only A Game; Freak Out

description:
In 2005, IDW launched Angel: The Curse #1, kicking off a half-decade of Angel tales. Now, it all culminates in this FINAL ISSUE. Story threads dating back to After the Fall #1 all tie together in this explosive last hurrah for Angel and his team. Don’t miss your chance to say goodbye to the original vampire with a soul before he heads off into the twilight…

(Well, not quite “goodbye”… stay tuned next month for a special coda and the final issue of Spike, too!)

first_appearance_teams.name: Wolfram and Hart, Attorneys at Law

team_credits.name: Wolfram and Hart, Attorneys at Law

description: The unforgettable new sci-fi epic that asks the question: what makes us human? As the battle for freedom rages on, one clone discovers that sometimes what makes you human is your willingness to fight for what is right. But sometimes that means the loss of the only world you have ever known. Discover a future where life is nearly perfect, but war continues to rage on, setting up the ultimate INSURRECTION!

It’s a whole new game for supervillain-turned-superhero Max Damage as he desperately tries to turn the tide of public outcry in the wake of the most challenging fight of his superhero career. But with his original sidekick, Jailbait, back in his life, and the secrets of supposed ally Alana Patel bubbling to the surface, Max will have to call on all of his strength to remain INCORRUPTIBLE. Mark Waid’s hit companion series to the Eisner-nominated IRREDEEMABLE continues in this must-have issue!

Stan Lee and Mark Waid continue their critically acclaimed time-traveling tour de force! Following the events of last issue, the Traveler becomes the prisoner of Anachronopolis, an otherworldly city where the past and future overlap. More twists and turns through time as revelations about the mysterious Traveler are revealed

Episodes 9-15

Episode 16: Bonus Chapter
name: Ancient Chinese Secrets

description:
Yomiko Readman's love for literature goes far beyond any run-of-the-mill bookworm's! In fact, she has a supernatural ability to manipulate paper in the most amazing ways. From turning a tiny scrap into a lethal throwing dagger to making a single sheet hard enough to block bullets, she's only limited by her imagination. She uses her phenomenal power to seek out legendary books containing secret information that in the wrong hands could be dangerous. Backed by a Special Operations Division in England, Yomiko has her hands full battling evildoers, saving the world, and trying to find time to curl up with a good book.

Episodes 17-23.
name: Reading Can Be Deadly

description:
Yomiko Readman's love for literature goes far beyond any run-of-the-mill bookworm's! In fact, she has a supernatural ability to manipulate paper in the most amazing ways. From turning a tiny scrap into a lethal throwing dagger to making a single sheet hard enough to block bullets, she's only limited by her imagination. She uses her phenomenal power to seek out legendary books containing secret information that in the wrong hands could be dangerous. Backed by a Special Operations Division in England, Yomiko has her hands full battling evildoers, saving the world, and trying to find time to curl up with a good book.

Episodes 24-30.
name: Dear Deadly Diary

description: Michelle is a romantic daydreamer and hardcore book collector. Maggie is a soft-spoken bookworm who always gets mistaken for a boy. Anita is an athletic tomboy who doesn't have time for reading. Together, they're the Paper Sisters, three very different siblings united by a strange power. Michelle, Maggie and Anita all have the ability to control paper in any way they desire. And from their Hong Kong detective agency, they solve any and all cases involving books! The much-anticipated follow-up to the hit series Read or Die!
name: The Clock Strikes

description:
Maggie always gets absorbed in whatever she's reading. But when she gets her hands on a book called The 24 Faces of Maggie Mui, she starts transforming into one character after another! Also, Anita and Maggie come up with a bibliophilic exercise plan for a suddenly pudgy Michelle, Anita visits a mixed-up fantasy world populated by characters from children's books, and the sisters are hired as bodyguards for a very unusual author...which leads them to another confrontation with Lily the Reader Extraordinaire!

Chapters 16-23
name: Many Maggies

description:
For love of books or love of money (to buy books), the Paper Sisters will take on any job. But as bodyguards for Hisami, a child-prodigy author, they may have bitten off more than they can chew. To protect Hisami from a shady stalker, Michelle, Maggie and Anita will have to call upon all their paper powers--and the bonds of their sisterhood. Also, the sisters' past is revealed for the first time...and a certain fellow Paper Master makes a special appearance! Don't miss the conclusion of Read or Dream!

Chapters 24-31 & The Final Chapter.
name: The Last Chapter

description: Two young Celestials get into a debate about who the superior life form is on prehistoric Earth, the Small Folk or the Killer Folk. But when the ferocity of Devil Dinosaur proves no mach for the savage Killer Folk, a savage from the future is brought back to even the odds. It's the battle you thought you'd never see: HULK VS. DEVIL DINO by the Eisner Award Winner of The Goon, Eric Powell. Plus THE FIRST APPEARANCE OF THE HULK-- NO LIE! "I Was a Slave of the Living Hulk!" From Journey Into Mystery #62, November 1960 by Jack Kirby/Dick Ayers.
Reprints Marvel Age: Spider-man Team Up #1.
name: Marvel Adventures: Spider-man and Fantastic Four

volume.name: Marvel Adventures: Spider-man and Fantastic Four

description:
The Silver Surfer has lost his emotions and memories and is on Earth in the hopes of regaining them as he once had on the planet. Over the Himalayas, he is drawn to a strange power. He finds a temple and enters it, finding himself in front of a massive presence, the energy he had sensed. Somehow, the being awakens. 
 
The being is known as Scrier, and it talks with the Surfer for a bit before grabbing hold of him and adding some of the Surfer's life energy into his own. He encases the Surfer in the temple and leaves to view how the Earth has changed while he slept. The Surfer manages to free himself and engages Scrier in battle, believing him to be a threat to Earth.  
 
Scrier stops the battle and reveals that he is responsible for the past and future of Earth. He claims to be able to restore the Surfer's memories and emotions. He also claims that he can return Zenn-La. He will do these things if the Surfer agrees to serve him. The Surfer agrees, but first he is put to a test. 
 
The Surfer flies to Chicago to obtain a baby named Edward Cross. His mother, Emily, has two other children and her husband has left her. She is also addicted to heroin. The Surfer comes and takes the baby from her, but she leaps out the window in an attempt to stop him. She pleads with the Surfer to not take her baby and that she may not be the best mother, but she loves her children. The Surfer returns her baby and uses his power to help her with her addiction. This action causes Scrier to appear. 
 
Scrier has already been betrayed by the Surfer. He cannot serve him and Zenn-La is to remain dead. The Surfer reveals that it was envy that caused him to return her child. As he leaves, Scrier wonders if the Surfer really failed his test at all.
name: The Awakened!

description:
Buddy & Lisa — back to Seattle! In the first full-length Buddy story in ten years (and it's a doozy), just when things are starting to look idyllic for our heroes, a family crisis forces Lisa to re-unite with her Seattle-based parents and brings Buddy and their young son Harold along with her — and Buddy quickly learns why she's been avoiding them for 20-odd years! And Lisa has some other unwelcome surprises in her family tree as well...

Plus, Pete gets political in cartoons from El Rios, High Times and Seattle Weekly. And a couple of ads!
name: Heaven

description:
The Silver Surfer is visiting the Hawaiian island of Kahoolawe when a pair of Ice Giants attack. He is able to stop them and travels to find Thor for answers as to how they got there. 
 
He approaches Avengers Mansion and meets with Thor. Thor informs him that Asgard has been destroyed and the Surfer agrees to help him find out who is responsible. They start their travel through time but an unknown force stops them, leaving them in another realm. They are attacked by some sluglike creatures and the Surfer is captured. 
 
The captor is Millenius and he needs the Silver Surfer's Power Cosmic to free himself from his banishment. He believes that all mortals should be killed which is why he was banished from Asgard in the first place. Thor battles with Millenius while a machine siphons the Power Cosmic from the Surfer to create a portal.  
 
The Surfer manages to escape but he cannot close the portal. He asks Thor to help close the portal while he engages with Millenius. Thor successfully closes the portal and he and the Surfer team up on Millenius. They cannot defeat him, but they can momentarily stop him long enough to travel to their own realm. 
 
Exhausted, Thor and the Surfer part ways.
name: Millennius!

description: The Marquis continues his crusade against the escaped souls of Hell! Amidst a rash of killings, Vol de Galle is on a race to catch a devil who uses the townspeople for murder, then commits suicide to escape into another body. How can the Marquis stop a killer that kills itself?

It was during the 18th century that the Ministry of Inquisition ruled over the lands of Venisalle. In the world of the Marquis, faith is not only the religion but the strict law of life and death. It is into this world that the souls of Hell have escaped to sin, murder, and be free within the possession of the living. During this time one man has been `blessed` with the ability to see into the very souls of the damned and fight the demons within. But as the Marquis begins his holy crusade to send back the escapees of Hell, the lines of good and evil begin to blur into a struggle between faith and sanity.

Work of Belgian comic book writer - Jean Van Hamme. Epoxy tells the story of a young girl who've been teleported to the Ancient Greece. She encounters many mythical creatures and try to survive. Volume contains mild nudity scenes.
name: Epoxy

description: If there was one thing the Convict Commandos — Jelly Jakes, Smiler Dawson, Titch Mooney — liked, it was easy money. Unfortunately the money their leader Guy Tenby had them chasing wasn’t easy, it was very difficult indeed. For it was in Nazi-Occupied Norway and the Nazis didn’t want them to get anywhere near it...
name: Blood Money

description:
Five hundred years before Columbus, barbaric Viking invasions ravaged North America.

Pathfinder is the story of a young Viking boy left behind as the only survivor of a shipwrecked expedition. A stranger in a strange land, the boy is raised by a tribe of American Indians--the very people the Vikings had sworn to destroy. When Vikings again storm the eastern shores, waging another barbaric campaign, they slaughter the tribe that adopted the young man. Now he wages a violent personal war to stop the Viking's trail of death and destruction.
name: OGN

description:
Veteran war reporter Fred “Ferret” McGlone celebrates his landmark 100th birthday in style — and reminisces about his earliest days as a roving newshound on the shady, cobbled back streets of Victorian London.
Naturally, that’s only the half of it. What about Ferret’s thrilling adventures on the high seas? Or his dangerous despatches from the front line chaos at the heart of the British Empire in India?
name: Rebellion in the Raj - Ferret's Mutiny

description:
Many and fearsome are the perils that can beset a man on a swift-flowing river after dark.
Japanese river patrols knew all these dangers, but armed to the teeth they feared none of them.
Then, one dark night, there glided into that gleaming river a new menace that was to strike terror into every Jap soldier…a swimming Irishman with hatred in his heart and a Commando knife between his teeth.

Originally Commando No.8.
name: Red Runs the River

description:
They floated out of the sky into the fields of enemy-occupied France. For this crack team of British paratroopers it was the moment of truth.
Dropped miles from their objective, a handful of determined men on their special Wellbikes set off to complete their mission. The odds against them were incredible but they had no alternatives. The fight was on...

Originally Commando #1402 and re-issued in Commando # 2740.
name: Paratrooper

description: MUTANT X writer Howard Mackie reveals untold secrets of the series' most popular characters! As hinted in MUTANT X #16, Bloodstorm and Gambit share a painful past. Now, their shocking secrets are exposed as we learn why these two mutants are eternally connected! Also, what happened to this world's Jean Grey? Without Professor X and Scott Summers in her life, what became of Marvel Girl?
name: A Sinister Thread / Thieves in The Night / First Blood

description: Continued from MUTANT X #31, the end is near! One by one, the MUTANT X world's most powerful heroes are falling! Only one person is capable of saving both the planet of The Six and our world. His name is Havok. Fear him. And fear for him!
name: The Key

description:
Plot Summary

While the Flaming Carrot is busy giving a rousing and "inspirational" speech to the Woman's Legion of Decency club he is informed that the town is being attacked by a killer Santa Clause. Using his wits, charm and super-hero team up skills he might defeat the group of Killer Santa's while fighting alongside a new up and coming rock group, Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets.

Are these unlikely heroes up for the task or is the Flaming Carrot going to meet one ho-ho-horrible end?
name: Flaming Carrot & the Invisible Jackets

first_appearance_teams.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

team_credits.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

name: Flaming Carrot and Reid Fleming, World's Toughest Milkman

description:
Plot Summary

The Flaming Carrot is back and ready for action! Armed with his not so trusty Baloney Gun he fights two crooks by the name of Garbagemouth and Bambo! Will he succeed or is his new weapon going to be the death of him?

This issue also features the rise of a tribal group of individuals known as The Pigmies, who are they, what do they want and why are they building a large replica of the human ear out of paste and french bread while in the middle of the woods?

(Note: This is issue 33 in the main series)
name: Flaming Carrot Goes PC!
